-- Kenya Gets $149 Million AfDB Loan for Power Projects, Daily Says
-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 2011-12-30T07:19:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-30/kenya-gets-149-million-afdb-loan-for-power-projects-daily-says.html
Kenya ’s state-owned Geothermal
Development Co. received a $149 million loan from the  African
Development Bank  to develop 400 megawatts of power generation,
 Business Daily  reported.  The loan was approved under two separate arrangements, with
$124 million coming from the African Development Fund and $25
million from the Climate Investment Fund, which is implemented
by the African Development Bank, the Nairobi-based newspaper
said, citing Hela Cheikhrouhou, the bank’s director for energy,
environment and climate change.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
